  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guinea RHR project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Guinean Red Cross is a key player in the national system of response to emergencies in Guinea. In the response to the epidemic of Ebola the CRG provided leadership of the Hygiene and Sanitation Commission in addition to the services usually offered to communities in responding to emergencies. Community health is one of the three pillars of its strategic development plan 2015-2020. This project aims to increase the resilience of the communities in the region of Moyenne Guin&#xE9;e toward diseases with epidemic potential. The GRC are currently the best placed actor in Guinea to implement community-based health programs including community based surveillance through their network of volunteers trained in first aid disaster management and PHAST and their experience in social mobilization and management of several pillars of intervention against Ebola The project will support the development of a strong RC volunteer and health worker network to implement community-based surveillance systems The GRC approach is in line with the National Plan to strengthen epidemiological surveillance developed by the Ministry of Health in Guinea. This project is one of the components of a larger reproductive and sexual health programme implemented by the GRC and the Danish Red Cross since 2009 in Moyenne Guin&#xE9;e. A consortium will be formed with Danish and Swiss Red cross Danish Red Cross being the lead agency.</narrative>
  </description>
